src/lib/components/DashPaperdragon.react.description: OpenSeadragon and PaperJS Component that allows Dash to interact with the OpenSeadragon viewer

id.description: The ID used to identify this component in Dash callbacks.

config.description: config is a dictionary of options for setting up the component and initial rendering

zoomLevel.description: zoomLevel of the current OSD Viewer

curMousePosition.description: Current Mouse Position in Image Coordinates

viewportBounds.description: viewportBounds of the current OSD Viewer

outputFromPaper.description: data sent from paper back to dash

inputToPaper.description: data sent from dash to paper

tileSourceProps.description: sent from dash to update x offset, y offset, rotation, or opacity of the image

baseImageWidth.description: This is the width of the base image, which is the first image in the tileSources array

viewerWidth.description: The width of the viewer in pixels

viewerHeight.description: The height of the viewer in pixels

curShapeObject.description: This is the last shape object that was hovered over

pixelColor.description: This is the last pixel color that was hovered over

setProps.description:
Dash-assigned callback that should be called to report property changes
to Dash, to make them available for callbacks.
